  "prompt": "Does Indian Institute of science provide plagiarism check for outsiders?",
  "response": "The **Indian Institute of Science (IISc)**, Bangalore, primarily focuses on academic and research activities for its students, faculty, and affiliated researchers. While IISc does use plagiarism-checking tools like **Turnitin** or other software for academic purposes, these tools are generally reserved for internal use, such as checking the work of students, faculty, or research scholars within the institute.\n\nFor **outsiders**, IISc typically does not provide plagiarism-checking services. If you are an outsider and need to check for plagiarism, you would need to use other publicly available tools or services such as:\n\n1. **Turnitin** (if you have access through your institution or a subscription)\n2. **Grammarly** (plagiarism checker)\n3. **Copyscape**\n4. **Quetext**\n5. **PlagScan**\n6. **SmallSEO Tools**\n\nIf you require an official plagiarism check for a specific purpose (e.g., publication), consider reaching out to professional plagiarism-checking services or your own academic/research institution. For IISc-specific queries, you may contact their administrative office to confirm if any services are available for external users.",
